We complete the proof of the Archimedean case of Ostrowski's Theorem for the rational numbers:
```lean
theorem mulRingNorm_equiv_standard_of_unbounded (notbdd: Â¬ âˆ€ (n : â„•), f n â‰¤ 1) :
    MulRingNorm.equiv f mulRingNorm_real
```

This concludes the proof of the theorem:
```lean
theorem mulRingNorm_equiv_standard_or_padic (f : MulRingNorm â„š) (hf_nontriv : f â‰  1) :
    (MulRingNorm.equiv f mulRingNorm_real) âˆ¨
    âˆƒ! p, âˆƒ (hp : Fact (p.Prime)), MulRingNorm.equiv f (mulRingNorm_padic p)
```
